Digital Logic Vault: FSMs, Buffers, and Protocol Decoders
"This repository contains a comprehensive collection of digital design and verification projects implemented in Verilog/SystemVerilog and verified using advanced methodology like UVM. The portfolio spans fundamental logic design to protocols, featuring synchronous FSM structures (Mealy/Moore) such as a 1101 Sequence Detector, a Traffic Light Controller with built-in timers, and an overflow-calculated Vending Machine. It also showcases data path units including a single-clock Synchronous FIFO Buffer with safety underflow/overflow logic, and a PS/2 Keyboard Receiver designed to decode serial keyboard streams with an integrated hardware filter that selectively captures and displays only specific character keys (A, B, and C) while filtering out unwanted noise or inputs."
